do you believe in science mysteries of the mind the mind is a general term that refers to the center of human thought individuality rationality and recall while the specifics of what the mind entails is open for debate most agree that it describes a set of functions that belong solely to humankind the mind is often associated with intelligence and it is common to hear mind power used interchangeably with brain power the brain can be explained with a concrete scientific definition however the mind can not how the mind works has remained a mystery for centuries and modern science continues to search for an explanation of this remarkable facet of human activity because the mind can t be understood in rational terms some suggest that the mind can travel beyond the realm of the body oftentimes supporters of this theory believe that humans possess supernatural abilities such as mind control and mind reading even more commonly many people feel that the mind can inexplicably operate in a subconscious state mind mapping is an example of this http www livescience com mind sometimes we engage in a method of thought and action that entails explanatoriness prediction and control and in which the relations among physical structures are measured empricially when we do this we are engaging in what we happen to call science so either science exists or we never engage in this method we do engage in this method so i have no logical choice it's a no brainer that if i did not believe in science then i'd be out of touch with reality in denying the existence of science Human Cognitive science Supernatural Scientific method Science Objectivist philosophy Intelligent design Mind Religion Reality Psychology Epistemology Free will Economics Quantum mind Meme Telepathy Falsifiability Mind control Artificial consciousness Creationism Deconstruction Philosophy of mathematics Logic Neuro-linguistic programming Consciousness Philosophy of language Causality Human nature Theory Unconscious mind Sou